[:subspace topology:]

Given a topological space $$(X, \tau_X)$$ and some $$Y \subseteq X$$, then the collection
$[ \tau_Y = \{ Y \cap U : U \in \tau_X \} ]$
is a topology on $$Y$$ which we call the \i[subspace topology].

Given a topological basis $$\mathcal B_X$$ for $$\tau_X$$, the following is a basis for $$\tau_Y$$.
$[ \mathcal B_Y = \{ Y \cap B : B \in \mathcal B_X \} ]$
